Oil traders in New York said ExxonCorp's Exxon U.S.A. unit reduced the price it charges contractbarge customers for heating oil in New York harbor 0.75 cent agallon, effective today.    They said the reduction brings Exxon's contract barge priceto 43.25 cts. The price decrease follows sharp declines inheating oil prices on spot and futures markets, traders said. Reuter&#3;